Idris Garba Kareka was, yesterday, returned as the speaker of Jigawa State House Assembly. Kareka, who is the immediate past speaker of the assembly, is the member representing Jahun Constituency. The new speaker was elected during the inauguration of the 7th assembly, and has since taken the oath of office. Liman Musa Kadara, member representing Guri Constituency, emerged as the deputy speaker. Kareka and his deputy were elected unopposed.  Jigawa assembly: Kareka emerges Speaker Tension in Jigawa assembly over new leadership My election, a surprise package by my colleagues – Jigawa’s new Speaker Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin